Nato led peacekeepers have urged Yugoslav authorities and ethnic - Albanian militants to keep talking to prevent a new round of fighting near Kosovo .
The tension began last week with <COREF ID="0" TYPE="IDENT">ethnic - Albanian rebels</COREF> attacking Serb positions in <COREF ID="1" TYPE="IDENT">the Presovo valley of Serbia</COREF> killing four Serb policemen .
The new democratic government of <COREF ID="2" TYPE="IDENT">President Vladimir Kostunica</COREF> agreed to give the alliance more time before launching counter attacks to drive out <COREF ID="0" TYPE="IDENT">the rebels</COREF> .
<COREF ID="2" TYPE="IDENT">Mr. Kostunica</COREF> visited <COREF ID="1" TYPE="IDENT">the valley</COREF> Monday and pledged to bring peace to <COREF ID="1" TYPE="IDENT">the area</COREF> .
